Subject: Fix ssd_run_scenario.tmbfit to pass fitted estimates to the rng call

ssd_run_scenario.tmbfit() computes the estimates from the tmbfit via
ssdtools::estimates() into a local `args` variable, but the recursive
call to ssd_run_scenario() does not pass `args = args` through, so the
recursion falls through to ssd_run_scenario.character -> .function
with args = list() (the default). The rng function therefore runs with
no parameters and produces samples from the default distribution
(e.g. rlnorm(n, meanlog = 0, sdlog = 1)) instead of the fitted one.

ssd_sim_data.tmbfit() handles this correctly, so the bug only manifests
via the run-scenario path. The fix is one line: thread `args = args`
into the recursive call. The added regression test compares the data
produced by ssd_run_scenario(tmbfit) to the data produced by
ssd_sim_data(tmbfit) under an identical seed; these should be
byte-identical and were not before the fix.

The two scenarioTMB2 snapshot files are regenerated because the bug
fix changes the values the existing "ssd_run_scenario.tmbfit works"
test produces (e.g. the HC est at proportion=0.05 goes from 0.145 to
8.90 because samples now reflect ccme_boron's log-normal estimates
instead of standard log-normal).

Apply with: git apply scripts/tmbfit-args-fix.patch
---
--- a/R/run-scenario.R
+++ b/R/run-scenario.R
@@ -165,6 +165,7 @@
   ssd_run_scenario(
     x,
     ...,
+    args = args,
     nrow = nrow,
     dists = dists,
     rescale = rescale,
--- a/tests/testthat/test-run-scenario.R
+++ b/tests/testthat/test-run-scenario.R
@@ -102,3 +102,17 @@
   scenario <- tidyr::unnest(scenario, cols = hc)
   expect_snapshot_data(scenario, "scenarioFit2")
 })
+
+test_that("ssd_run_scenario.tmbfit uses the tmbfit's fitted estimates", {
+  # Regression test: ssd_run_scenario.tmbfit computed the estimates from the
+  # tmbfit but dropped them on the recursive call, so the rng function ran
+  # with default parameters instead of the fitted ones. ssd_sim_data.tmbfit
+  # threads them through correctly, so the two paths should agree.
+  fit <- ssdtools::ssd_fit_dists(ssddata::ccme_boron, dists = "lnorm")
+  tmbfit <- fit[[1]]
+
+  via_run <- with_lecuyer_cmrg_seed(10, ssd_run_scenario(tmbfit, nsim = 2))
+  via_sim <- with_lecuyer_cmrg_seed(10, ssd_sim_data(tmbfit, nsim = 2))
+
+  expect_equal(via_run$data, via_sim$data)
+})
